    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tent roofs in the particular context of Russian architecture, characterized as being a tall four- or many-sided pyramid. The form first appeared in defensive structures and then spread into religious architecture, reaching an apex of development in 15th-16th century wooden architecture.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000132/Suzzallo-UW</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000048285/Azarov, Russian-English Encyclopedic Dictionary of Arts (2005)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In de Russische architectuur de benaming voor tentdaken in de vorm van hoge vier- of meerzijdige piramiden. De vorm werd voor het eerst toegepast bij verdedigingswerken en daarna ook in de religieuze architectuur, met als hoogtepunt de houten architectuur van de vijftiende en zestiende eeuw.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>俄羅斯建築中特有的帳棚頂，高聳的四角或多角錐狀為其特色。此形式最早出現於防禦性建築，後來延伸至宗教建築上，並於十五至十六世紀的木構建築上達發展高峰。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
